    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.4 \"α-Bungarotoxin (α-Bgtx) labeling of nAChR α9 and α10 in cochlear tissues and cultured cells\"\nAt P10 VAChT labeled presynaptic terminals overlap extensively with alpha-Bgtx staining. In cochlear hair cells the alphya-Btx staining is mediated by alpha9/alpha10 heteromeric nAHCRs.\n\nRapsyn, a component of the muscle postsynaptic specialization, binds and mediates aggregation of alpha-Bgtx (=alpha9/alpha10 heteromeric nAHCRs) in non-neuronal cells. This is another indirect indication of localization of alpha9/alpha10 heteromeric nAHCRs to the cholinergic postsynaptic specialization.\n\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: \"...we first investigated α-Bgtx labeling of nAChRs in freshly isolated cochlear hair cells from postnatal day P1 and P10 rat pups. \"",
